<center> 
<hr size="2" width="100%"><span style="font-weight: bold;">As a last image, only rarely are internal features of trilobites preserved, as in this specimen showing the</span><br style="font-weight: bold;">


<span style="font-weight: bold;">digestive tract and lateral caecae of <span style="font-style: italic;">Selenocoryphe platyura</span>, a ptychoparioid trilobite from Utah. Note</span><br style="font-weight: bold;">


<span style="font-weight: bold;">how the caecae become less prominent posteriorly, and disappear altogether by the middle of the thorax.<br>


</span><br>


